 The Chief Justice of Nigeria, CJN, Justice Tanko Muhammad, on Friday, swore in eight new Justices of the Supreme Court. The new Justices that took turns to take their oath of office and oath of allegiance to the Nigerian Constitution, were Justice Lawal Garba, North West; Justice Helen M. Ogunwumiju, South West; Justice Addu Aboki, North West; Justice I. M. M. Saulawa, North West; Justice Adamu Jauro, North East; Justice Samuel C. Oseji, South South; Justice Tijjani Abubakar, North East, and Justice Emmanuel A. Agim, South South. Their elevation has increased the number of Justices on the apex court bench from 12 to 20. By Henry Umoru THE Senate has confirmed eight Justices of the Court of Appeal as Justices of the Supreme Court of Nigeria. The confirmation by the Senate yesterday was sequel to the consideration of the report of the Senator Opeyemi Bamidele, All Progressives Congress, APC, Ekiti Central led Senate Committee… October 13, 2020 In "News" ... As Senators quarrel over mode of Screening By Henry Umoru The Senate Wednesday raised the alarm that poor salaries for Judges and Justices was exposing them to temptation of being involved in taking bribes from politicians and well placed citizens. According to the Senate, with the poor remuneration packages… October 7, 2020 In "News" The National Judicial Council (NJC) on Thursday recommended four Justices of the Court of Appeal to President Muhammadu Buhari for appointment as justices of the Supreme Court. Mr Soji Oye, Esq, the Director of Information disclosed this in a statement in Abuja. Those justices recommended for Supreme Court appointment include… October 24, 2019 In "News"